########################################################
# Peasy is easy
########################################################

INSTALL:

1. Compiling and Installation in Linux:

1.1. Install dependencies:

     You need additional packages to compile "Peasy".

     Just type these commands:
     
       sudo apt-get update
       sudo apt-get install build-essential bison flex autoconf git-core libtool 
       sudo apt-get install python-wxgtk2.8 python-wxtools python-jsonpickle
       sudo apt-get install python-numpy checkinstall pyro python-pymodbus
       sudo apt-get install python-pip python-nevow python-twisted python-soappy
       sudo apt-get install python-psutil ncurses-dev python-dev python-wxglade
       sudo apt-get remove python-serial
       sudo pip install pyserial


     If you are using a 64Bit Ubuntu based distribution,
     then you have to install the package "ia32-libs" too.

       sudo apt-get install ia32-libs

1.2. Compile and install "Peasy":

     There is a self written bash-script, which helps.
     
     To compile and install this application type this:

       1. cd /path/to/espees_v0.2/
       2. sh make.sh -m Peasy
       3. sh make.sh -i Peasy
